# Documentation Update Policy

- Avoid creating new documentation files (README, CHANGELOG, API refs, etc.) when refactoring, adding features, or fixing bugs unless the user explicitly asks for them.
- Update existing documentation as needed to keep current files accurate, but avoid introducing new documentation unless specifically requested.
- If documentation changes are required, limit edits to the relevant existing files and describe any need for additional docs and request approval before creating them.
- Exception: when creating a brand-new extension, required baseline files mandated by `extension_structure.mdc` (for example extension metadata/docs scaffolding) are allowed.